## Input
```python
lazy import foo
lazy    import    foo,    bar as baz

lazy from a import b
lazy from some.really.long.module.name import first_really_long_name, second_really_long_name as renamed_value
lazy from a import (  # comment
    bar,
)

def f():
    lazy import foo.bar
    lazy from another.really.long.module.path import first_name, second_name as alias
```

## Outputs
### Output 1
```
indent-style               = space
line-width                 = 88
indent-width               = 4
quote-style                = Double
line-ending                = LineFeed
magic-trailing-comma       = Respect
docstring-code             = Disabled
docstring-code-line-width  = "dynamic"
preview                    = Disabled
target_version             = 3.15
source_type                = Python
nested-string-quote-style  = alternating
```

```python
lazy import foo
lazy import foo, bar as baz

lazy from a import b
lazy from some.really.long.module.name import (
    first_really_long_name,
    second_really_long_name as renamed_value,
)
lazy from a import (  # comment
    bar,
)


def f():
    lazy import foo.bar
    lazy from another.really.long.module.path import first_name, second_name as alias
```
